<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 8:15AM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Locally Intense Snow Showers...
Scattered snow showers will affect the area through 10 AM before
diminishing. Some of these snow showers will drop a quick dusting
of accumulation and will result in brief reductions in
visibility. These snow showers will impact the I 69 corridor
between Lapeer and Port Huron and the I 94 corridor between Port
Huron and Mount Clemens. Drivers are urged to proceed with caution
in this area.</description>
